As a new user of RStudio, there are several important ideas that I learned in Module 1. Such as: Setup RStudio panes, using Markdown to reproduce documents, create webpages in GitHub which is a community for R programming users, have learned basic R syntax to produce the project as required, edit HTML, YAML and CSS.

For further learning, I am curious about lots of things related to data technologies. Most interested is data visualization by using ggplot (or any updated packages available). Others are about import and tidy data, transformation and exploration of data, modelling data, how R program deal with large data sets, etc.
